SSL: encryption (encoding the info), identification( sending to right pc)
Using ssl: noone can see the data passed on to other pc.
https: handshake:
1) computers agree on how to encrypt
2) Server sends the certificate
3) Your computer says : Begin encrypting"
4) Server says: "Begin encrypting"
5) All messages are now encrypted.
Version of ssl, random number: to compute master secret/ encryption keys, key, cipher, hash
Server sends certificate with public key.
